springVersion = "Now is the critical hour of decision, when the fates of both our kingdoms hang in the balance. You are clever—cleverer than your father. That is why I know you will not fall at the fins of Selkie capital. You will not be bribed out of your honor and compassion. I would not be so brazen if I suspected otherwise.

As the situation is severe, I must be brazen. The Selkie domination of our economy—obtained through the flagrant disregard of environmental protection policy—has begun to encroach into our political system. I have recently received confirmation that Lord Theobald and his co-conspirators attempted to steal my democratically-elected seat of power.

 Cleary, tensions between Selkie and Merfolk will boil over in Pelagis any day now. In yours, the populace is undeniably agitated after a year of unprecedented hardship. I believe we each have the keys to solving each others’ problems; all we must do now is take each others’ hands with confidence and the resolve to do what is right."
